FATEs_Notorious monster_Blood, Augur, He: The Immortal Flames have pinpointed the whereabouts of one Blackbile Maladd Chahâ”€an Amalj'aa hexweaver thought to be behind the assassinations of several high-ranking flame officials. Track down the terrible warlock and send him back to the Lifestream.
FATEs_Notorious monster_Bump and Grind_D: The Brass Blades seek volunteers to aid them in the capture or slaying of Corpse Brigade captain Gisfrid the Grinder.
FATEs_Notorious monster_Quenching the Fl: Members of the notorious Flamefang Amalj'aa have assembled in Zahar'ak in preparation for their next raid. Now is the time to strike a blow against these fanatical servants of Ifrit. Defeat the Flamefang commander and his elite minions.
FATEs_Notorious monster_Return to Cinder: The Zanr'ak altar is used to augur the outcome of future battles between the Amalj'aa and Ul'dah, and it is Cindersoot Pegujj Chah who throws the bones. Slay the mesmerizer and see that his fortune-telling days come to a bloody end.
FATEs_Notorious monster_Spark off the Be: Whitespark Hepugg Rohâ”€an eagle-eyed Amalj'aa archer with the strength to pierce three Immortal Flames with a single arrowâ”€has been sighted lurking nearby. Hunt down the named fiend and see that his sharpshooting days are through.
FATEs_Slay enemies_An Inconvenient Truth: A unit of well-trained Amalj'aa known as the Gore Horde has been dispatched from their homeland Paglth'an with a single purposeâ”€to lay waste to close-lying Ul'dahn settlements. Intercept the unit and wet the sands with beastman blood.
FATEs_Slay enemies_Downwind_Desc: A pack of violent sandskin peistes has been drawn to Little Ala Mhigo by the stench of the latrine pits which surround the mesa caves the Ala Mhigan refugees call home. While many of the settlers can hold their own in a fight, the sheer number of peistes may prove too much for the encampment.
FATEs_Slay enemies_Fallen Corpses Writhe: A band of zombies has been exhibiting uncharacteristically civilized behavior of late, which has greatly unnerved the people of Thanalan. Dispatch the dapper undead for the benefit of the living.
FATEs_Slay enemies_Fish out of Water_Des: During the Calamity, the land's aetherial balance was disturbedâ”€the result being a myriad of unexplained phenomena which has botanists and naturalists puzzled. What the scholars can agree on, however, is that the balance must be restored, and that means eradicating the problems as they emergeâ”€and anglers in the desert certainly can be classified as one of those problems.
FATEs_Slay enemies_Gyve Talk_Desc: The Amalj'aa of Zahar'ak have begun gathering troops outside the 1st Gyve in preparation for what can only be a march into Ul'dahn territory. Break their ranks and send the beastmen scattering.
FATEs_Slay enemies_Harder, Bigger, Faste: After years of experimentation, Amalj'aa beast tamers have finally perfected a new breed of biologically augmented drakes and have moved to testing the creatures in the field. Use this opportunity to slay the war creatures before they are taken back to their cages.
FATEs_Slay enemies_Heroes of the 2nd_Des: The Immortal Flames 2nd Main Brigade is moving to assault an Amalj'aa strongpoint and seeks reinforcements to help prevent its ranks from being flanked by the enemy.
FATEs_Slay enemies_Tempered, Tempered_De: Instead of killing his victims, Ifrit will â€œtemperâ€ them, burning away their wills, rendering them mindless servants to the Lord of the Inferno. As a primal is only as powerful as the number of its followers, returning the souls of the tempered to the Lifestream effectively weakens the demigods.
